inn1.comm: fires it full outside off, the batsman comes forward and leaves it alone
back of length outside off, the batsman dabs it towards point
comes forward and defends the length delivery to the off side
keeps him in the crease with a short of length delivery, the batsman defends it towards point
length delivery on the stumps, the batsman defends it down the pitch
first short ball of the morning and Hafeez knows they are going to be plenty of them, so he swivels and whacks it to the backward square leg boundary
full and on the pads, comes in a touch and the batsman tucks it past midwicket for his first runs
gets a nice bit of shape into the batsman, starting from off and coming in, but Hafeez, somehow, manages to flick it behind square leg. He was not in control there.. the bat rotating in his hands
now pushes it wide outside off, the batsman leans into it and nudges it to mid off
full and on the pads, the batsman flicks it down to deep backward square leg with ease
bowls it with a grunt but it's a bluff as this one is a touch slower, the batsman defends it to point
angled away from the right-hander, Hafeez leaves it alone
length delivery outside off, draws the batsman forward. Shehzad pushes it towards point
goes back and across and defends the 141 kph length delivery down towards the bowler
the short-ball plan again results in a big top edge but there is no one at deep square leg! Neesham has to cover a lot of ground from fine leg but Shehzad was definitely hurried into the pull
angled into the pads, Hafeez pushes it to wide mid-on for a quick single
goes a touch wide outside off to tease the batsman, Shehzad comes forward but leaves it alone belatedly
short ball again, Shehzad goes for the pull again, mistimes it again... it lands way short of fine leg again. That's not the last bouncer we will see today.
goes back and across to defends the length delivery to the off side
comes forward and punches the length delivery to the off side, finds the fielder at cover
looks to push it towards cover again but plays marginally outside the line, ends up pushing it back down the pitch off the inside half of the bat
gets a freebie and carves it to the boundary. It was a wide full-toss and all the batsman had to do was slice it in the gap at point
short ball outside off, Mitch Mc's pace is not going to cause many problems, this is almost pulled off the front foot, through midwicket

now this is easy for the batsman, he is getting into his groove to hit the pulls and he crashes this to deep backward square leg. Neesham is there, but his knee gets stuck in the turf as he goes for the slide, ends up parrying it to the boundary
four boundaries in four ball for Pakistan! But this one is off a thick outside edge.. It was not too far from a diving Guptill's left hand at gully
could have been the fifth one! Hafeez punches this length delivery down the pitch but hits the stumps at the other end
calmly leans into this length delivery and punches it to mid-on
angles it in from wide of the crease, defended towards mid-on
slightly wider outside off, the prof leaves it alone
leans into this.. just timing. He comes forward and places it in the gap at extra cover. Williamson chases it down
back of length delivery, the batsman pushes it towards mid-off and wants a single.. but sends Hafeez back as he sees the extra cover fielder intercepting it..
stays in the crease, defends the length delivery to the off side

he dabs this one towards extra cover and takes on the fielder! This is a proper sprint from Shehzad.. He needed it .. a direct hit and he was nowhere. Nathan Mac misses it this time unlike the previous time
superbly punched through midwicket! This is just a punch.. He stays back and clips it off his pads to the boundary.
not his best shot today.. This is a thick top edge off a bouncer but this lands just short of the boundary at fine leg.. It went very fine
it's raining in Sharjah! He creams this fuller delivery through covers now. Another hat-trick of boundaries for Mitch Mc
more runs.. this one is fired full on the pads and all the batsman has to do is place it to the left of square leg for a few more runs
length delivery outside off, pushed to cover
doesn't move his feet but this one is timed beautifully! He just opens the face to place it to the left of the short cover fielder and it races along the turf
out of the ground! Shehzad was waiting for this.. It's not too short but Shehzad swivels and whacks it over midwicket for a huge one.
length delivery on the stumps, the batsman tucks it to midwicket
little bit of width and Shehzad crashes it behind point for more runs.. this time the fielder at third-man slides and cuts it off
tight line around off stumps, the batsman defends it calmly
waits in the crease and defends the back of length delivery towards point
short balls not creating any impressions tonight.. This one sits up at a nice height and that's swatted over the deep backward square leg fielder for a flat six
length delivery outside off, the batsman leaves it alone
it's the fuller length that does the job! Professor moves forward to push this firmly through cover but this goes away with the angle, catches the outside edge and a simple takes for the keeper
rises up with the short of length delivery and defends it to the off side
back of length just outside off, defended towards gully off the back foot
stays in the crease and punches it firmly to cover
leans into this length delivery, punches it on the up but is not able to find the gap at cover
fires this full and in the blockhole, the batsman digs it out to mid-off
he plays a neat upper cut but probably missed out on a boundary. That was short and wide, but he plays it straight to third man
fuller and just outside off, Younis leaves this one alone
looks to glide this one down to third man but misses
repeats the shot he tried to play last ball and succeeds this time, steers it to third man
fuller and outside off, the batsman comes forward and punches it to short cover
full and wide outside off, Younis doesn't bite it.. lets it go through
comes forward and pushes the length delivery towards mid-off
hops on the crease and punches the length delivery straight to cover
slightly wide outside off, the batsman slaps it straight to point
comes forward and guides the length delivery down to third man

he opens the face of the bat at the last moment to place this short of length delivery through the gap at cover point.. Nicely placed. Guptill chases it down, pulls it back.. then Anderson throws in a slide too, to prevent it from hitting the boundary a second time.. Good tandem effort
comes forward and punches this on the up to cover

big hesitation! Shehzad pushes this to mid-off and starts sprinting but Younis hasn't moved an inch.. Shehzad comes down halfway before turning back.. A more accurate through would have had him in trouble
length delivery outside off, punched to point
he wanted to thrash this widish delivery through cover, but this one slides under the bat.. no bounce there at all.
looks to punch it down the ground but doesn't get the timing.. Works perfectly as it gives the batsmen enough time to take a single to mid-off
sharp bouncer.. This one gets up quickly and first time in the day, the batsman doesn't go for a shot.. He sways away from the line
waits in the crease and chops the length delivery down to third man

goes back and across and punches it towards extra cover.. The fielder gets a bad bounce and doesn't stop it cleanly.. That fumble almost did Shehzad as he thought there was a single and started moving. But mid-off was alert and fired a quick throw.. Another miss for New Zealand as this would have been out had he hit
comes forward and pushes this length delivery down the pitch
comes forward and defends the length delivery to the off side
keeps it tight around the middle stump, the batsman defends it to midwicket
wants a single to the off side but this is placed straight to point
full and wide outside off, Shehzad has lost a bit of touch as he misses out.. Gets no timing pushing this to cover
back of length on off side, dabbed straight to point
fuller and wider outside off, the batsman drives this one nicely but there is protection in the deep

superbly timed down the ground! The mid-on fielder was a little wide so there was no one to stop this firm push down the ground. It's a no-ball as well as Neesham's foot has flicked the bails off. Not a free hit
length delivery outside off, the batsman nudges it straight to backward point
short delivery, comes a touch slow for the batsman, Shehzad rolls his wrists on this as he pulls it to deep square leg
he leans forward and pushes the length delivery towards mid-off
superb fielding by Williamson at mid-off, dives to his left and cuts off a neat push that was headed for the boundary
blazed away behind point as soon as there is sign of width. Keeps an opens stance and slaps this length delivery through off. No chance for third man
tries to repeat the shot but gets an underedge to the off side
short delivery and the batsman is judging them well.. Leaves this one alone as it's high enough to be called a wide
length delivery on off, he stays rooted to the crease but punches it to deep cover with ease
pushed full on the stumps, Shehzad calmly nudges it through square leg
looks to whip the back of length delivery to the leg side but gets hit on the thigh pad
he comes forward and punches the length delivery to mid-off
a bit more intent this time, but he is not able to find the gap.. Punches this to mid-off again
he gets into a tangle as he plays this pull shot from outside off. Possibly it was the lack of pace on it.. Rolls it down to deep square leg
keeps using his good eye to punch on the up, he is not going towards the ball, just using his hands. Crunched to deep cover
slides it across the batsman, who plays a lazy push and is beaten
stays in the crease and defends the flatter delivery to the off side
fuller and flighted outside off, he comes forward and drives it straight to cover
width provided and Shehzad chops it behind point, but Anton Dev dives to his left to cut it off. Shehzad misses out on a boundary there
wants a single to the off side but he plays it straight to cover
slower and tossed up on off, he comes forward and eases it to long off
shortish delivery on the body, the batsman clips it off his hips down to fine leg
shuffles across and punches the back of length delivery to midwicket
goes back and across and whips it to the right of midwicket for a quick single
angled in to the batsman who goes back and dabs it to midwicket for a quick single
back of length outside off, the batsman hops on the crease and defends it down the pitch
comes forward and pushes the length delivery to cover
slow and loopy on off, the batsman has to wait and defends it to off
crashed through cover to bring up his half-century. That's a fantastic stroke. It was quicker and fuller outside off and he square drives it just in front of point
slower and on the stumps, defended to the leg side
flighted on the stumps, tucked to midwicket
comes down the crease and pushes the tossed up delivery to the off side
makes room and punches the flatter delivery to long off
fuller on the stumps, the batsman pushes it to mid-off, who is a bit deep, to scamper though for a single. There was some hesitation for a bit but that is comfortably done
on the pads and Younis shuffles across to clip it fine down the leg side for his second boundary
fuller on the stumps, the batsman punches it firmly but straight to mid-off
he gets squared up a touch as he tries to turn the length delivery to the leg side.. ends up pushing it to cover
full on the stumps, Younis looks for an on drive but cannot beat the fielder at mid-on
on the pads, Younis walks across and clips it to fine leg for a single
short delivery again, the batsman gets cramped as he goes for a ramp.. it hits the glove, then the helmet, then rolls to the off side
much slower and on the middle stump, the batsman punches it to cover off the back foot

slam dunk! This is massive from Shehzad. He comes down the pitch and even though he not close to the pitch of the delivery, he carries through with his shot.. that has gone out of the stadium, over cow corner. They have lost the ball there. Some cow is going to graze on it now
tossed up outside off, the batsman pushes it straight to cover
flatter outside off, the batsman goes back and across to punch it to long on. That's fifty of this partnership
now Younis steps out but this is too full, he punches it down the ground, past the non-striker for a couple
shorter and flatter outside off, the batsman punches it to deep point
fuller and on the stumps, Younis punches it back to the bowler
flatter and outside off, this time Younis pings the gap. There was enough time to place it anywhere. He cracked it off the back foot through extra cover.. No chance for the fielder in the deep
flatter and on the stumps, punched back to the bowler
slower and wider outside off, the batsman slaps it to deep cover
flighted and on the stumps, the batsman defends it solidly as if his life depended on this one shot

oh superb effort at the cow corner by Latham.. But this is just out of the reach. Younis stepped out, wasn't to the pitch of the delivery but went through anyway.. doesn't get the timing but finds the boundary
no question about this one! This is a powerful mow from Younis and this has gone deep into the stands at cow corner
now he smartly tucks it to square leg to roll the strike over
comes down the crease but the bowler slows it down, the batsman has to defend
flatter and quicker on the stumps, punched down to long on
this is a waste of a wicket! Younis tries to go downtown again but doesn't get hold of it, holes out at long-on
comes from round the stumps and pitches it just short of length, the batsman defends it solidly
gets off the mark with a soft dab towards mid-on
fuller and on the stumps, the batsman pushes it to cover
no feet movement, but he punches this on the up straight to cover
short ball from round the stumps, Shehzad has been playing the pull nicely, flat-bats this one to deep midwicket
crisply hit through the gap at cover! he leans forward and punches it through the tiny gap for a couple of runs
goes back and punches the flatter delivery to long on
slower and loopier on off, the batsman defends it down the pitch
much slower this time, the batsman comes forward much before the ball arrives, defends it to the leg side
stays back and punches it to wide long-on
quicker one on the pads, clipped away to deep backward square leg
slower from the bowler, defended to midwicket
tapped to the right of cover, Shehzad has judged this single far better. Guptill was the man there and he's not the easiest to take on
leans into a picturesque drive, but he can't beat the field. Extra cover backtracks for a bit of cushion
shortish and outside off, defended
there's the customary short ball, it would seem, but Shafiq too is willing to take it on. Pulls and keeps it down to deep square leg
lets the fuller ball outside off come on and opens the face, but he finds Taylor at gully
laced through the covers as this gave Shehzad the width he needed. New Zealand though have a man out of the boundary
flighted outside off, Shehzad lunges forward and drives to cover
flatter on off stump, Shehzad goes back and punches to short midwicket
looks to run the good length ball towards third man, but the late cut fails as he plays a bit inside the line
backs his strength as he comes down the track, reaches the pitch and drives the ball over extra cover. Lovely stroke!
nudged to short midwicket
gets down, but N Mac has seen it and pulls his length back. Shehzad is happy to push it down to long-on
steps down to a length ball and squirts it away to deep midwicket. Useful inside edge
stays balanced at the crease and slices the ball to point
full and a shade outside off, he bunts it down to mid-on and sets off early enough to beat the mid-on rushing in
good length ball outside off, chopped into the covers
goes short, but this pitch is no longer conducive for that line of attack. Sits up for Shehzad at waist-height and it's been clobbered to the midwicket boundary
opens the face this time, and again he doesn't quite need footwork to be as solid as he is. Single to third man
comes forward and pushes this to cover point

goes well across the stumps to paddle this but it rolls of his pads to short fine. Loud appeal for lbw.. it looked like the impact was just outside off.. New Zealand will review it. Yeah, the impact is well outside off. It would have hit the middle stumps but that doesn't really matter
comes down the crease but is not to the pitch of this delivery, defends it towards midwicket
flatter on off, he goes back and punches it to cover  for a quick single
goes down on his knee and drags this tossed up delivery from outside off to deep square leg
short and wide, Shafiq misses out as he crashes this straight to cover
length delivery outside off, it is steered down to third man
full and wide, the batsman leans into it but cannot find the gap, hits it straight to cover
keeps it tight around the off stump, Shafiq defends it down the pitch
gets some room and crashes this to deep point off the front foot
superbly hit over the bowler's head! That was full outside off and he swings it straight down the ground
stays back and dabs this length delivery straight to point.. But a poor throw from Guptill allows a single
full and flighted on off, driven firmly to cover
moves towards the off side and nudges the flatter delivery to backward square leg
looks to pull this long hop but it not only stays low, it turns too.. hits the batsman on his pad
tossed up on the stumps, the batsman comes forward and defends
comes down the pitch but can only dig it back to the bowler
pushed through on the stumps, punched down to long on
a misfield at cover allows a single after the batsman has pushed it off the front foot
looks to steer it through point but is not able to beat the fielder
full and wide, the batsman goes low on his knees and crunches it to deep cover
back of length on the stumps, Shafiq dabs it to midwicket for a quick single, has to dive to get in at the non-striker's end
superb timing! That has been crunched beautifully.. It's short and wide, yes, but he places it expertly in the gap between backward point and deep point.

dropped by the keeper.. A really really (Misbah would say) tough chance low to his right. The ball was coming in from round the stumps and it got a big deflection from the bat, so the keeper had to adjust, go the wrong way.. He gets a hand to it but is not able to complete it. Difficult chance
full and flighted on the stumps, pushed to long on
he goes back and dabs it towards midwicket for a single
comes out of the crease and whips this to deep midwicket
slower, loopier and wider, the batsman has to wait before dabbing it in front of point
a long hop that doesn't bounce much, the batsman still adjusts well to flick it fine on the leg side. He was initially looking to pull
full and flighted on the stumps, pushed to midwicket
dabs this in front and wants a single, but gets back as the bowler gets to the ball in no time
stays back and opens the face to run this down to third man
he is cramped for room as this one keeps coming in to him, pushed back down the pitch
sees the width and throws his bat at it, but it doesn't bounce much.. slides under the bat and reaches the keeper on the bounce
length delivery on the stumps, the batsman pushes it with soft hands towards mid-on for a quick single
cracked off the back foot but a Guptill dive at point prevents this from running far
slower and on the stumps, the batsman pushes it to midwicket
very slow again, the batsman goes back and punches it to deep cover
full and flighted on the stumps, he comes forward and punches it to long off
comes down the pitch and eases the flighted delivery to long on
superb stuff from Nathan.. he dives across to prevent the punch going on to long on
loud appeal for caught behind as this one spins down the leg side.. Nothing on that
comes forward and pushes the flighted delivery to midwicket
length delivery on the stumps, tucked to midwicket
slower delivery outside off, the batsman spots it and flat-bats it down to deep midwicket
arches back and looks to cut it behind point but is not able to beat the fielder there
shuffles across and dabs it with soft hands to square leg for a quick couple of runs, moves to 99
there is it! His sixth century in ODIs, his second against NZ... He lets out a cry of joy. Excellent attacking innings from Shehzad. It came with a dab to third man.
he comes forward and punches this to mid-on
whoaa!! He is quick on his heels today.. Swivels and pulls the short delivery precisely in the gap between deep backward square leg and deep midwicket
wanted to go over the infield on off side but doesn't get any timing! It was short and wide.. He was planning to go over extra cover.. finds mid-off
swings his bat across the line on a length delivery, mistimes it to midwicket
digs this one short but Shafiq is quick on the pull, hits it straight to the man at deep midwicket
slower delivery outside off, Shehzad waits in the back foot and looks for that gap at point but is not able to beat the fielder
oh he miscues it over the bowler's head.. That went nowhere. It was a short delivery outside off, came a bit slow and he mistimes his pull
he comes inside the line and clips the back of length delivery off his hips down toe fine leg
he sees the length delivery and just chips it over mid-off.. It clears Williamson but wasn't too far.. not much timing there but it runs down the boundary
slower delivery on the stumps, Shehzad tucks it to square leg for a single
that is some proper connection! He moves to the leg side to give himself some room and hammers it over extra cover.. his first boundary
digs this one short, the batsman ducks under it
looks to punch this off the front foot but it bounces extra, pushed back to the bowler

he is gone, the brilliant innings has come to an end! It was short and wide, and like the last over, he wants to go over mid-off rather than through point.. It hits a bit high on the bat and the fielder at mid-off back pedals to take it easily
happy birthday! he has got two in two. This one is on a length and cuts in a touch.. enough to beat the lazy waft and smash the off stump
no problems in dealing with that, Sohail punches the length delivery to mid-on
superb start for Sohail.. He moves to the leg side and beautifully punches this with a straight bat through cover
more crisp timing! Rises with the ball and crunches it on the up to deep point
gets a short ball first up, he gets under it
back of length on off stump, the batsman punches it straight to midwicket
back of length and rising outside off, the batsman punches it on the up to cover
slower delivery on off stump, disguised with a grunt in the follow through, the batsman nudges it to square leg
full and on the pads, Lala tickles it down to fine leg
puts in the shoulder behind this short ball, it zips past the shoulder of the bat as the batsman misses the pull
wow! The bowler went round the stumps, dug it short on off stump but Haris was up to the task, carves the rising delivery over cover.. off the back foot
slower delivery outside off, the batsman pushes it to mid-off without any timing
shorter delivery outside off, Afridi looks to pull but doesn't get any timing, single to midwicket
he is looking good here, Sohail.. Moves slightly leg sidish to free his arms, whacks the length delivery to the leg side but there is protection in the deep
he doesn't care about the fielders.. Looks like he is beaten by the lack of pace on this short delivery but Afridi has easily cleared the square leg boundary
goes through point now! Short and wide, just needed to slap it in the gap
keep them coming! This is short outside off and Afridi smashes it over the cow corner or the camel corner or whatever.. the point is.. this has cleared the boundary easily again
back of the length on the body, the batsman clips it down to fine leg
no he won't .. keep swinging while you can. This is a length ball on the middle stump line and Afridi launches it over the umpire.. Not much timing but there is no one in the deep behind the bowler
full and wide outside off, Afridi looks to guide this fine on the off side but doesn't make any connection
well the last ball you want to bowl to him is a full-toss.. because he will butcher those all day. He drags it from wide outside off and sends it along the ground to the midwicket boundary
full and wide outside off, Afridi jams it out to point for a single
slower bouncer on the stumps, Sohail wanted to play the upper cut but makes no connection
doesn't get the timing as he drives this fuller delivery down to long on
whoa! Superb shot.. he moves to the leg side to give himself some room, gets a short one and bludgeons it over midwicket with a flat hit.
slower delivery on the stumps, the batsman punches it straight to cover
he looks to give himself some room by moving towards the leg side but the bowler smartly pushes it wide outside off. Left alone
still wide outside off, the batsman throws his bat at that but doesn't connect. Sohail looks at the umpire to check if it's a wide but the umpire shakes his head
this has to be a wide! The batsman was stepping out but this was way outside the line on off
slower delivery wide outside off, the batsman stretches out and gets an underedge fine on the off side. The fielder at third man prevents it from running to the boundary
no stopping Lala today! This is a slower bouncer, sits up nicely for Afridi and he flat-bats it over midwicket for yet another boundary
well wide outside off this time
whoa!!! This is a slower ball outside off, length ball.. Afridi waits and slaps it over mid-off.. He was on the back foot but this has sailed over the boundary. What power!
he reaches out to this fuller delivery and carves it over cover for a single to the sweeper
gives himself some room and crashes the length delivery to deep cover
a rare occurrence.. he is beaten outside off as this just cuts away from back of length
this is smart cricket! Delicately steered past the keeper.. It was very wide outside off and Lala runs it down with a cute little cut
makes the mistake of delivering a low full toss outside off, Sohail doesn't have to do anything fancy.. just leans into it and punches it through extra cover
on the stumps, the batsman punches it to mid-off for a single
superb yorker from Neesham. The batsman digs it out down the pitch but then Neesham allows the single by not bending down in time to stop that
looks for the yorker but it's a low full toss on the stumps, it's punched down to long on
sees the full toss early but it's a slower one.. he toe-ends it down to long on
another good delivery from Neesham, it's in the blockhole and the batsman can only squeeze it down to deep point
full and wide outside off, the batsman has to reach out but doesn't make any connection.. It's right at the border of that wide-marker
he comes down the pitch but the bowler pushes it wide again, the batsman gets a toe end to this as he tries to go over cover.. just lands behind the fielder
stands in the crease and punches the length delivery to point for a single. Guptill makes a diving stop and is in some trouble as his knee gets stuck. Seems ok..

he looks for the big hit by moving towards the leg side but makes no connection as this is wide outside off. The keeper doesn't stop it cleanly either. The bowler is surprised as this is called a wide
wide full toss, this one is crashed over over for a one-bounce four. Called a no-ball for height.. a bit harsh from the umpire though
looks to guide this slower bouncer past the short third man but he doesn't connect
no stopping these two! He moves to the leg side and whacks the length ball over midwicket with ease. Why not go for that wide yorker again?

another full toss but the batsman punches it straight to mid-off. This was as high as the previous one but the umpire is fine with the height. The umpires are checking for the height now.. It was pretty high but he was down the pitch too. So he will have to go.
goes forward and slaps the length delivery to long-on to bring up the 300 for the team

Ah hard luck, he will get a duck as a gift on his 100th game. Akmal was looking to do the right thing.. he dabs this to point to give Afridi the strike but his captain chickens out from the run as this has gone straight to Guptill. The fielder has all the time in the world.. he makes a run for the stumps and then hits them from a meter away.
back of length outside off, the batsman slaps it to mid-on for a single
watch this rocket away! Afridi slices it over point for a boundary to bring up his half-century.. his second in three games. Is this a new Afridi?
looks to cart this length ball over the off side but doesn't get much timing
pushes this wide outside off, but this is too wide
fuller and fired on the off stump, the batsman digs it out to deep cover
fuller delivery outside off, Lala gets a bottom edge to the leg side as he looks for the big heave
stands with an open stance but fails to make connection with this bouncer, he was looking for the upper cut
a slower bouncer now.. Sarfraz looks to pull but plays it too early, it hits the shoulder and rolls down to third man
full and wide outside off, Lala looks to crash it through cover but gets a thick outside edge to third man
goes down on his knee to play this sweep to the leg side but it's a shorter one, hits him high on the bat and rolls to the leg side

well well,  a bit of anti-climax here and Lala times this low full toss beautifully to Williamson at extra cover. He was standing at the edge of the circle and takes it low to his left. Afridi was eyeing that gap behind the fielder.
length delivery outside off, pushed to mid-off without any timing for a single
now Tanvir turns the strike over with a calm dab to mid-off
slower bouncer, the batsman pulls it down to fine leg
pushes it further away from the right-hander and this is called a wide..
length delivery on off, the batsman pushes it to mid-off
fires it in the blockhole, the batsman digs it out towards midwicket
he gets the slower delivery right in the slot and he is not going to let that go unpunished.. lifts it way way high and way way long.. over long on
full and wide, punched to mid-off for a single
he bowls a fuller one from round the wicket but this takes the deflection from the pads and runs down to the boundary.
good yorker from round the stumps, he appeals for an lbw.. Mitch wants a review.. Williamson says don't bother
another good yorker in the blockhole.. the batsman digs it out on the pitch and takes off
shorter delivery, Sarfraz smartly steers it over the short third man fielder
another boundary, this is short and Sarfraz is not going to miss out.. slaps it in front of square and beats the fielder in the deep easily
poor choice from Mitch.. he digs this one really short and it sails over the batsman. Way way over
superb yorker, just costs a single to mid-off. Makes you wonder why he doesn't bowl that more often
ooh lala! Tanvir gets it in the slot.. full and on off and he swings it over long-on with utter ease.
shorter delivery, he tries to repeat the shot but gets a top edge.. It lands at midwicket where there is no one.
gimme six more.. Length delivery, driven over long-off.. Just a neat little golf swing
slower delivery that sits up.. This is carnage.. Sarfraz flatbats it through midwicket. This is murder
now he sweeps, he loves to sweep.. he slogs it through midwicket for yet another boundary. What a finish for Pakistan!!

inn2.comm: gets nice movement away from the right-hander, Guptill lets it go through
right on line around off stump, the batsman comes forward tentatively and defends
keeps getting that away shape, Guptill uses his reach to defend this to cover
stands tall and punches this length delivery firmly to wide mid-off for a single. Good fielding by Younis there
stays back and punches the back of length delivery down the pitch
outswing, but this is well wide outside off and going further away
this one swerves into the batsman and strikes him on the pads. Tanvir asks the question for lbw but it seems this was going down
back of length and it rises chest high, the batsman defends it to point
nice channel outside off, the batsman watches it go through

just beats the outstretched hand of Wahab Riaz at mid-on! Guptill was going for the pull but this got big on him, it hits the splice and balloons down the ground but Wahab is not able to reach it. Poorly timed jump actually
fuller delivery and it hits the pads, the bowlers asks the question but that pitched outside leg
length delivery on the stumps, the batsman gets an inside edge on to his pads as he pushes from the crease
that's the first one! Devcich looks to pull the short of length delivery but only manages an inside edge that Sarfraz gobbles up with a dive to his right
length delivery on the pads, the batsman plays across the line and his hit on the pads.. that pitched outside leg
length delivery on the stumps, Guptill inside-edges this to his pads as he looks to push it to the off
another one hits the pads as Guptill misses an attempted flick.. Still pitching outside leg. The batsman picks up a leg bye though
still down the leg side, Williamson looks to flick but this flicks the pads and rolls to the keeper's left
length delivery on the stumps, the batsman leans on this and punches it back to the bowler
this time Guptill gets bat on the leg-sidish delivery and manages to place it to the left of short fine leg to earn his first boundary. New Zealand need a lot more of this
angled away from the right-hander, the batsman lets it go through
back of length and on the pads, Williamson tucks it to square leg for a single
he gets squared up as he comes forward to defend this length delivery
leans into the length delivery and punches it through wide mid-on for three runs
nicely rides the bounce to chop the rising delivery down to third man
he pushes it to mid-off with soft hands and calls early for a quick single
he is keeping it tight around off stump.. the batsman wants to watch the swing, and so, he is playing late, punches it to mid-on
looks for the inswing but this is down the leg side
oh wow Younis! He slides to his right from mid-off and fires a quick throw at the non-striker's.. just misses by a nanometer.. Guptill would have been a gonner
stays upright and punches the length delivery to cover
he comes half forward and punches the length delivery down the pitch
comes down the pitch and looks to drive the length delivery through cover, but misses it completely
clips it beautifully off his pads to pick up a couple to deep midwicket. He allowed the ball to come in and just at the last moment, used his wrists to punch it away

game over for Guptill! This is back of length and going away from Guptill.. he looks for the pull again, gets a top-edge again. .This one lobs towards cover where Afridi runs in and takes a smart low catch
keeps the batsman on the back foot with a sharp rising delivery, defended to gully
more of an outside edge as Taylor pushes at this length delivery, runs it down to third man
stays on the back foot and defends this back of length delivery solidly
nicely played by Williamson as he chops this short of length delivery to point, straight to the fielder though
now he finds the gap! This is wide enough for him to free his arms and he pings the gap at cover point
he looks to punch it off the back foot but chops it to short cover without any timing
clips this one off his pads to pick up a single to deep square leg
lunges forward to punch this length delivery to mid-off
stays back and stylishly punches it off his pads to pick up two more to deep midwicket
he comes forward this time and punches the length ball to mid-off
keeps playing this punches beautifully but most of them are going to the fielders.. this one straight to cover
on the pads, Taylor pushes it through midwicket for a single
and again, he punches it beautifully off the back foot but straight to cover
this was one of the better placed punches, but this time Shafiq's dive at cover cuts it off. Still no respite for Williamson, just a single
tall bounce there.. Taylor wanted to upper cut that but can't reach it in time
angled in on to the pads, Taylor shuffles across to dab it to midwicket
stays back and dabs it towards cover with soft hands for a quick single
gets forward to a good length ball and runs it to point

oof! Saw the ball full and he pounced on it as if he was afraid Irfan would never bowl another fuller ball ever. The cross-seamer has been lashed over the straight boundary, and he hit it so hard that the ball sailed away even after it hit the bottom of the bat
good length on off stump, Taylor is tight with his defence
bangs in short and Taylor, who was camping on the back foot, has hooked the ball to long leg. Took it from outside off, and it had a lot of height as well. Looked a bit of a top edge
back of a length and outside off, Williamson stands up tall and punches to mid-off. Younis won't let it pass again.
gets down, but is given another shortish ball which he can only push to short cover
slices a shortish ball outside off to Shehzad at point
slants it quite wide outside off, Taylor looks to lash it over the off side but can't reach. Umpire allows it
this time he's made contact! And how! Another cross-seamer which offers ample width again and Taylor capitalises over extra cover.
back of a length and right on off stump keeps Taylor pinned to the crease and quiet

outside edge this time, and it sails over the third man boundary! Phew! How fast must Wahab be bowling for that to carry just off his own pace. And perhaps it was a short boundary as well. It was full, it had width again and Taylor benefits because of his intent. Another cross-seamer, by the way
141kph, shortish and on the body, tucked to deep square leg
pushed through on middle and leg, Taylor taps it into the leg side and seeks a single. Take a couple of steps, and then decide not to risk it
stays back to a shortish delivery on off stump and slices it to deep point
mild appeal from Afridi as Williamson gets down and is stuck on the front pad. He was trying to flick, but the bat was way outside the line
flighted on off stump, defended
gets down the track, but the ball goes on with the angle and takes the inside edge as Williamson was looking to flick it. Gets a single to fine leg
pinned on the crease and struck on the pads, but this skidder would have gone down leg
pacy delivery on off stump, 147 kph, Williamson punches it through cover off the back foot
slashes at this as soon as he sees width, but there is protection at deep point
full and wide outside off, the batsman doesn't get close to the line but throws his bat, the thick outside edge carries it over backward point and through to the boundary
stays back and whips it with the angle to deep midwicket
he is leaking runs here.. This is marginally outside off and we know how much Taylor likes to cut and chop.. this is breezy once it leaves the bat and scurries through point
now slightly shorter and this too races to third-man.. Fast hands from Taylor, he is not holding himself back
that was expected, the double S - Shahid Slider! This keep's sliding in and Taylor doesn't really have the space, or the right length, to cut it.. It sneaks in and flattens the middle stump.
tossed up on off from round the stumps, defended down the pitch
there he goes, sweeps it from wide outside off and plays it down to fine leg
short and wide, the batsman misses out a touch as he pushes it straight to cover
quicker one on the pads, Williamson punches this to midwicket
he leans forward to this tossed up delivery and defends it to off
starts off with a bouncer this time.. the batsman ducks under it
stays back and dabs this short of length delivery to the right of point
back of length delivery on the stumps, he stands tall and punches it to deep cover
back of length on the stumps, he hops on the crease and whips it to deep midwicket
comes on top of this length delivery and defends it to cover
back of length outside off, Latham calmly steers it to third man
goes back as this is shorter and wider outside off, chops it to deep backward point
plays it off the straight bat unlike Taylor, punching the slider towards long off
waits in the crease and cuts this wider delivery to short third man
as soon as this is tossed up, Latham goes for the sweep and hits it straight to backward square leg
flatter now, defended off the back foot

good shout for lbw as Latham misses his sweep shot of a quicker and fuller delivery.. Maybe there was an inside edge there, otherwise it looked pretty good. Signalled a leg bye though.. Hmm. Replays shows it was heading way down
he comes forward to this back of length delivery and carves it past a diving point fielder for a couple down to third man
attempts the bouncer but this is misdirected, goes down the leg side
comes forward and punches the length delivery to point
brings it in and the batsman tucks it through midwicket for a single

superb shot! He stands tall and punches the length delivery past the stumps at the non-striker's.. Superb timing there as this just keeps speeding along. That was rising on him, but he still manages to stay balanced
gets a thick outside edge down to third man
back of length on off, the batsman defends it towards point
gets down the track and whips the length ball from off stump to cow corner. And manages to hit it all along the ground.
pushed through and skids on to middle and leg, Williamson tucks it to short midwicket
gets down the track and has to block a flatter delivery on off stump
advances and yorks himself on leg stump, but since he had made room he is able to drill the ball towards point
good length ball on off stump, pushed back at the bowler. Williamson keeps looking at his left glove for some reason. Is his bat slipping out of his hands?
short, and it stays rather slow to foil Williamson's cut
oh, top class shot through the covers! Reaches forward to the pitch of a flighted ball and caresses it through the gap on the off side. Beautiful cricket shot
length ball on off stump, he goes back to clip into the leg side
tossed up outside off, Latham pulls out his pet sweep to long leg
backs away and pummels a shortish ball from outside the off stump to the extra cover boundary. Again, top class footwork against spin
gets down and whips the flighted ball on off stump to long-on
goes back, but is cramped up and decides against the cut. Punches with a straight bat and finds the bowler
drags this short and Williamson pushes off his front foot, goes deep in his crease and pulls the ball to the midwicket boundary. This is good batting against spin
nips down the track and lifts the flatter delivery outside off and chips to long-on
goes around the wicket to bowl a flighted ball a shade outside off, Latham pushes down to long-on
flat and straight, Williamson taps the ball back at the bowler
down the track and whipped over short midwicket. And once it lobs that man there is no one in the deep. What timing and placement.
pushed through on leg stump and Williamson plays around it. The flick doesn't connect, he is struck on the pads, but it would have gone down
flatter on the stumps, punched down to long on
easy pickings for Williamson as he bunts this shorter one to long on
he is never far away from a sweep, picks it from well wide outside off and smashes it to deep square leg
uses his feet but is beaten by the length there, gets a thick inside edge to short fine
comes down the pitch and caresses the fuller delivery to long off
goes back to the flatter delivery and punches it to deep cover
flatter outside off, Latham is beaten as he goes back to play the cut
tossed up wider outside off, the batsman dabs it towards cover with soft hands for a single
here comes the slider and the batsman gets a thick inside edge on to his pads
comes down the pitch but looks to play straight, drives it down to long off
fuller delivery on the stumps, Latham sweeps but cannot beat the man at short fine leg..
shorter and quicker, Latham is quick to slap that behind square for a single
comes out of the crease but is beaten in the flight.. this almost squeezes in .. The inside edge takes it to the pads, then to short third man
curtains for Williamson! Sohail keeps making an impression as a bowler.. Williamson wanted to push it down the ground but plays it a little early and Sohail gleefully accepts a low catch.
tossed up outside off and this is driven down the ground.. hello hello.. there is too much behind this drive.. the long-on fielder had no chance

game over! not quite.. Sir Faraz gets under this swirler but goes swirling himself.. he is nowhere near the ball..gets into a tangle. The batsman went for a slog sweep and got a thick top edge towards short third man. Weird drop that. Easy chance if you have gloves in hand.. still easy if you don't have them
tucked to the leg side for a single
looks to sweep this fuller delivery but bottom edges it on to his pads
fuller and on off, the batsman gets a thick outside edge down to short third man
tossed up on the stumps, the batsman defends
this could have been close! Anderson chips it right back but this is only a meter to Afridi's left
stays back and punches the flatter delivery to long on
allows this one to turn in, then clips it to fine leg for a single
no half-measures from Anderson.. he sees his width and he goes for a big booming drive. That flies through to the extra cover boundary
uses a straight bat to drive this tossed up delivery off the front foot through to deep cover
tossed up wide, the batsman waits and slashes it behind point for a couple more
flatter and honing in on off, the batsman comes forward and defends
comes down the pitch to this wide delivery, gets too close and bunts it back to the bowler
this is looped up in the slot and Anderson is not looking for the slow move.. he is not going to miss out, swings it over midwicket with a clean swing
flatter, chops it to point off the back foot
sliding down the leg side, this hits the pads and rolls to short fine leg
length delivery on the stumps, dabbed away to midwicket for a quick single
pounds this on the pitch and the batsman does well to get out of the way
hits the thigh pad now with that acute bounce. It's just not physically possible to get that kind of bounce for anyone else in the world
fires it in the blockhole now.. Smart bowling form Irfan. The batsman somehow digs it out
comes besides the line of the ball and carves it down to third man
back of length outside off, Latham steers it down to third man with ease
keeps it tight around off stump, Anderson comes behind the line and defends

there goes another one! Anderson's hit out approach was always going to be fraught with risk.. he goes for a pull to one that is not short enough, gets a thick top edge that lobs up for Afridi at mid-on
weird shot! Latham was going down as he played this pull but get a thick top edge behind the keeper for four. He really got into a tangle there
another short ball, the batsman pushes it in the air towards the bowler
serves up a short and wide delivery to end the over, this is easily crashed through backward point
there is a slip in place but that wouldn't help as this top edge needs two Irfans.. At Irfan's pace, these just fly off the edge
slower delivery on the stumps, the batsman defends it down the pitch
stays back and steers the back of length delivery to point
beats the batsman with the angle! Ronchi is stuck in the crease, expecting the shorter one
bouncer this time, Ronchi ducks right under it, but this is a touch down the leg side
another one down the leg side, easier call for the umpire
stays back and opens the face of the bat to dab it towards cover point
he is cramped for room as this short delivery keeps coming in but manages to swat it down to fine leg

loud appeal for caught behind! Sarfraz is convinced, the bowler is convinced... Wahab runs all the way to the keeper. But they don't review.. Interesting. They were dead sure. It was a good delivery.. Short outside off, moving away to beat the batsman's waft. No bat on it
length delivery on the stumps, the batsman dabs it to backward square leg
full outside off, it's a slower delivery, the batsman steers it down to third man
back of length on the pads, easily clipped off the hips to fine leg
oh that was not too far from the off stump! The batsman looks to cut this length ball but there is no room on it, slides between the bat and the pad
fuller and wider outside off, the batsman crashes it to deep cover
tossed up on off, the batsman defends it down the pitch

he gets a wicket second ball! Shehzad takes off like Shoaib Akhtar.. it's his first ODI wicket. It was tossed up on the stumps, the batsman sweeps and makes good connection, but this is hit straight to deep backward square leg
tossed up on the stumps, the batsman punches it down to long off
flatter, turns in sharply from off, Neesham dabs it to square leg
tossed up nicely on off, the batsman is unsure of the spin, comes forward and defends to midwicket
loopy on off, Neesham squeezes it to deep extra cover for a couple
flatter and shorter on off, punched straight to cover
slower this time, the batsman pushes it towards wide mid-off for a single
this is quick capitulation. The batsman comes down the pitch and drives it straight into the hands of mid-off. No elevation on that at all. Another catch for Wahab
flatter on the stumps, pushed to mid-on
stays back and punches the flatter delivery to deep cover
this is a long hop outside hop, Ronchi waits on the back foot and powers it to wide long-on where Wahab cuts it off
beautifully bowled! This drifts in, then turns away to catch the outside edge.. Runs down to the boundary
big turn for Shehzad again, the batsman pushes it to cover
tossed up on the middle and leg line, the batsman defends it down the pitch
loops it up too much, the batsman takes it on the full and swats it to deep midwicket
full and flighted on off, the batsman defends it towards point for a single
clears his front leg and drives the flighted delivery powerfully to long off
he gets his front leg out of the way and slaps it past the non-striker.. no one's going to stop that
goes back and punches the flatter delivery to deep cover
full and flighted, whipped away to deep square leg for a single
that's a powerful drive! It's flat outside off, but Ronchi punches it on the up.. it races away to the boundary at wide long off
shouts of catch it as the batsman punches it in the air towards cover but it just drops short of Younis
stays back and punches the flatter delivery to the off
whoa! This looked like a top edge but this goes flat and quick over long off. Super slap that one
goes back to nudge this one away to the leg side but gets a leading edge to off
flighted on the pads, the batsman drives it to wide long on for a couple
flatter now, this one is played towards wide long-on with soft hands  and they scamper back for two. A poor throw yields an extra run
tossed up on the stumps, the batsman defends it towards point
gets a thick outside edge to backward point as he looks to carve it inside out.. Lands short of the fielder
pushed to cover for a quick single
flatter on the stumps, the batsman tucks it away to deep midwicket
moves to the leg side and drives this flighted delivery firmly to long on

superb catch by Younis at extra cover! And Haris keeps increasing his tally of wickets. Nathan wanted to slog it over midwicket, the bat turns in his hands and the leading edge lobs towards extra cover.. Younis was at cover, but makes a quick move towards his right to catch it on a full stretch
almost takes his partner out with the drive! Henry moves out of the way just in time
on the pads, the batsman wants to nudge it to the leg side but misses it, gets hit on the pad
flatter on off, the batsman bunts it through cover for a single
stays back and pushes the slider down to long on
slower and turning away, the batsman punches it to deep cover
last one turned, this one comes in.. Henry was jittery on the crease, plays outside the line and loses his offstump to the googles.
tossed up on the stumps, the batsman defends
fuller on off, the batsman pushes it down the pitch
length delivery outside off, steered straight to point
whoa! That's some shot.. It's short of length and the batsman swivels to whack it over wide long-on.. Just a short-arm jab
now he moves his front leg out to hammer the length delivery over the non-striker for four more
superb slower delivery, it just misses the off stump after the batsman is beaten
bowls a slower yorker, the batsman digs it out down the pitch
moves to the leg side and punches this fuller delivery firmly to midwicket for a single
comes forward and cuts this powerfully but can't beat point
cuts this one from in front of off, played straight to the fielder at point
clears his front leg and squeezes it out to deep midwicket
whoaaa! He comes down the pitch, is beaten as this is wide and full, still manages to reach out and hammer it through wide mid-off
whoaa! He goes for the switch-hit.. paddles it down to short third man
quicker delivery on the stumps, catches the inside edge and runs to short fine leg
comes down the pitch to Riaz but doesn't get hold of this big shot.. bunts it to midwicket
he makes a good connection in this drive but hits it straight to cover! Moved his front leg out and punched it off the middle
he manages to squeeze out the fuller delivery to third man
slower delivery outside off, the batsman pushes it to extra cover for a quick single
fires it in the blockhole, the batsman digs it out comfortably
looks to reverse-paddle the fast bowler! Makes no connection though.. He was meaning to play that off the backside of the bat..Interesting.. very interesting
pushed through outside off, cracked off the front foot to short third man
that's the end! Afrid's 14th wicket for the year. He tosses it up and the batsman misses his slog.. It hits the off
